WRITING.TITLE: PS4 Refuses to connect controller in safe mode.

WRITING.TEXT: I #8217;ll start from the beginning in this thread.

Eight hours ago my PS4 was working fine, I had a loss online in a match and took a nap to cool off. But before leaving to take the nap, I tried to play another game. Then it told me that the game was corrupted, this confused me since I was playing it forty minutes before. So I did what the error message told me to, deleted and reinstalled. But then the download also went down too, saying the data was corrupted. I was getting frustrated, and had a good feeling I #8217;d need to restart the PlayStation, go into Safe Mode and rebuild the database, so I went and did that. Now here we are at this very screen. #8220;Cannot start the PS4. #8221; #8220;Connect the DUALSHOCK 4 using the USB cable and then press the PS button. #8221;

I got even more heated and decided to take a nap, the sun has gone down and I went back here to find my PS4 still in this state. Let #8217;s get into the crap I #8217;ve done so far to tackle this problem. - I changed USB cables, all of them are working properly and can charge Android devices with no hassle or fancy gymnastic positioning to start charging. (Total of three cables.) - I have used all existing ports available, the two at the front and the one at the back next to the HDMI slot. - My problem is not to do with any update, 8.00, 7.50, 7.00 - although I have been forced to reinitialise and rebuild my PS4 20+ times. - My PS4 came into my possession after 24th of March, 2015. Bloodborne was among the first games I played and the most memorable. Roughly speaking my console is around five years give or take, not counting production in whatever factory it came out of.
